%F A007590 a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-2) - a(n-3) + 2 = 2*A002620(n) = A000217(n+1) + A004526(n). - _Henry Bottomley_, Mar 08 2000
%F A007590 a(n+1) = Sum_{k=1..n} (k + (k mod 2)). Therefore a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} 2*floor(k/2). - _William A. Tedeschi_, Mar 19 2008
%F A007590 From _R. J. Mathar_, Nov 22 2008: (Start)
%F A007590 G.f.: 2*x^2/((1+x)*(1-x)^3).
%F A007590 a(n+1) - a(n) = A052928(n+1). (End)
%F A007590 a(n) = 2*a(n-1) - 2*a(n-3) + a(n-4). - _R. H. Hardin_, Mar 28 2011
%F A007590 a(n) = (2*n^2 + (-1)^n - 1)/4. - _Bruno Berselli_, Mar 28 2011
%F A007590 a(n) = ceiling((n^2-1)/2) = binomial(n+1, 2) - ceiling(n/2). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Mar 08 2014, Jun 14 2013
%F A007590 a(n+1) = A014105(n) - A032528(n). - _Richard R. Forberg_, Aug 07 2013
%F A007590 a(n) = binomial(n,2) + floor(n/2). - _Bruno Berselli_, Jun 08 2017
%F A007590 a(n) = A099392(n+1) - 1. - _Guenther Schrack_, Dec 10 2017
%F A007590 E.g.f.: (x*(x + 1)*cosh(x) + (x^2 + x - 1)*sinh(x))/2. - _Stefano Spezia_, May 06 2021
%F A007590 From _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 20 2022: (Start)
%F A007590 Sum_{n>=2} 1/a(n) = Pi^2/12 + 1/2.
